**ðŸŽ¯ Key Achievement: Enum Delegation Pattern**

The current implementation demonstrates the **enum delegation pattern**:
- âœ… **State classes** act as facades that delegate to **enum methods**
- âœ… **Abstract `getEnum()` method** in base classes ensures type safety
- âœ… **Business logic centralized** in enum classes (`UserStateEnum`, `PostStateEnum`)
- âœ… **External API unchanged** - Spatie ModelStates still works identically
- âœ… **Backward compatibility maintained** - no breaking changes to existing code

**Benefits achieved:**
- ðŸ”’ **Type safety**: Impossible to have invalid states (enum validation)
- ðŸŽ¯ **Single source of truth**: All state logic lives in enum classes
- âš¡ **Better performance**: Enum comparison is faster than string comparison
- ðŸ› ï¸ **IDE support**: Full autocompletion and refactoring capabilities
- ðŸ§ª **Easier testing**: Centralized logic means fewer test cases needed
